## Workflows

### Config changes (skills, CLAUDE.md, hooks, ai-context, openspec)
Edit in repo → `bash install.sh` → `git commit`

### Memory capture (periodic)
`bash sync.sh` → `git add memory/` → `git commit`

### New machine setup
`git clone <repo>` → `bash install.sh`

`install.sh` is repo-authoritative: copies everything repo → `~/.claude/`.
`sync.sh` captures memory only. Never run it for config changes.
